1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,794
<i>I found a prosecutor who can help us</i>

2
00:00:02,877 --> 00:00:04,629
<i>push through with our cases against Anton.</i>

3
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:07,757
<i>It shouldn't have come to this</i>

4
00:00:07,841 --> 00:00:09,175
<i>if you just did what you promised!</i>

5
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:12,429
<i>I told you from the beginning</i>
<i>that woman was no good for you.</i>

6
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:14,431
<i>This is all your fault!</i>

7
00:00:14,514 --> 00:00:15,890
[Mel] <i>Are you sure about this?</i>

8
00:00:15,974 --> 00:00:17,350
<i>If you post this online,</i>

9
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:19,519
<i>you'll be going</i>
<i>through the same toxic bullshit</i>

10
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:20,812
<i>that I've been going through.</i>

11
00:00:20,895 --> 00:00:23,106
<i>We may disagree on a lot of things,</i>

12
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:25,567
<i>but this, we're a hundred percent on this.</i>

13
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:28,570
<i>Mel, I don't know why you're doing this.</i>

14
00:00:28,653 --> 00:00:29,821
<i>I just want to let you know</i>

15
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:31,072
<i>that I still love you, Mel.</i>

16
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:32,991
<i>I'll help you guys find Edong.</i>

17
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:35,160
<i>What about admitting to what we did?</i>

18
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:37,245
<i>What? We'll get on the camera</i>

19
00:00:37,328 --> 00:00:39,205
<i>and tell everything on social media?</i>

20
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:41,374
<i>No, we'll hold a press conference.</i>

21
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,001
<i>I can't do it, okay?!</i>

22
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:44,753
<i>I can't do what you want!</i>

23
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:49,048
<i>I just want to correct their mistakes.</i>

24
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:51,968
[screaming]

25
00:00:53,511 --> 00:01:00,143
[theme music playing]

26
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:10,547
[crickets chirping]

27
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:15,593
[eerie whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]

28
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:24,978
[Ryan] You bastard!

29
00:02:25,061 --> 00:02:27,021
[panting]

30
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:28,148
Go away!

31
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:30,775
Love? Love…

32
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:32,110
- Love.
- [gasps]

33
00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:34,237
Love, it's just me. Calm down.

34
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:37,490
[panting]

35
00:02:37,574 --> 00:02:39,784
[stammering]
Where's Chloe? Is she all right?

36
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:41,327
We're all okay.

37
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:44,914
Love, don't worry.

38
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:47,667
There's a police
patrol making rounds here.

39
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:50,211
Erica made sure of that.

40
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:54,549
[exhales deeply]

41
00:02:59,637 --> 00:03:01,306
[door knob turns]

42
00:03:01,389 --> 00:03:06,644
- [eerie music playing]
- [door creaking]

43
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,236
[Chloe screams]

44
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:19,866
[eerie music continues]

45
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:23,036
Chloe, are you okay?

46
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:25,079
[breath quivers]

47
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:27,957
[music fades]

48
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,043
[breath quivers]

49
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:32,378
[uneasy music playing]

50
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:35,256
[breathes deeply]

51
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:40,637
When I saw the lifeless cat, Ma…

52
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:43,765
I was terrified.

53
00:03:43,848 --> 00:03:45,266
[screams]

54
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:53,733
That's over now, Chloe. You're safe.

55
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:56,152
Your Papa and I are right here.

56
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,362
[breath quivers]

57
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:01,574
I felt so scared that time, Ma.

58
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:04,661
But now…

59
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:07,413
I'm angry!

60
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:10,875
- [uneasy music continues]
- [sobs softly]

61
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:12,919
Why is he doing this to us?!

62
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:18,967
Yes, he went to prison,
and he was probably innocent,

63
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:20,677
but that doesn't justify what he's doing.

64
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:26,015
Because you were mistaken as well, right?

65
00:04:27,183 --> 00:04:31,771
It wasn't your fault
the police were so bad at their job!

66
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:34,941
[Chloe exhales]

67
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,653
[Louisa] <i>You're greedy!</i>

68
00:04:38,736 --> 00:04:40,071
<i>You're a liar!</i>

69
00:04:40,154 --> 00:04:42,407
<i>Didn't my brother tell</i>
<i>you over and over again</i>

70
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:45,994
<i>that the watch found in</i>
<i>the house wasn't Louisa's?</i>

71
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,745
<i>He stole it from someone else,</i>
<i>and that's the truth.</i>

72
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:49,414
<i>Yet you still lied, didn't you?</i>

73
00:04:49,497 --> 00:04:52,375
<i>And you, Beth, you were the first to lie.</i>

74
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:57,046
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
dark instrumental playing]

75
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:17,650
[music fades]

76
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,569
[Erica] The police will
be watching over your house.

77
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:22,405
But if possible,

78
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:26,326
stay inside for now.
We need to be careful.

79
00:05:26,951 --> 00:05:28,328
Don't go out alone,

80
00:05:29,037 --> 00:05:32,623
and if you must go out,
make sure someone knows your whereabouts.

81
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:37,587
Hold on, why can't the police
just catch Edong right away?

82
00:05:38,337 --> 00:05:39,964
Edong's very good at hiding

83
00:05:40,631 --> 00:05:42,675
and evading those who are after him.

84
00:05:43,843 --> 00:05:45,762
He's also very patient,

85
00:05:46,262 --> 00:05:48,347
so he can drag his scare tactics on.

86
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:53,186
I think that's what he wants.

87
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:58,858
But the police are
doing all they can to find him.

88
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:04,322
[somber music playing]

89
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:14,040
But Doc, you said all
the tests were clear, right?

90
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:16,876
Why do we have to wait?

91
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:18,836
[doctor] <i>There's a waiting period</i>

92
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:22,799
<i>for obtaining a U.S.</i>
<i>travel clearance, Mrs. Miller.</i>

93
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:25,009
<i>That's the protocol.</i>

94
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,053
<i>They want to be thorough.</i>

95
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:30,056
But my son needs to get
back to the U.S. immediately.

96
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:32,892
Is there really no way to speed things up?

97
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:34,811
[doctor] <i>I'm sorry, Mrs. Miller,</i>

98
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:37,021
<i>but you'll just have to wait.</i>

99
00:06:38,272 --> 00:06:39,649
[huffs]

100
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:45,822
[somber music continues]

101
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:47,073
[clicks tongue]

102
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:52,286
[music fades]

103
00:06:55,331 --> 00:06:58,417
I just want them to get
back there as soon as possible.

104
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:00,753
Why does even that seem so hard?

105
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:04,507
Alice, are you sure
you don't want to go with them?

106
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:07,009
I… I can't, Uncle.

107
00:07:07,635 --> 00:07:09,762
But you and Auntie… [sniffles]

108
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:12,515
Are you sure you don't
want to stay at my house?

109
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:15,017
- I mean, you're safer there.
- [sighs]

110
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:17,395
I can't move your aunt.

111
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:19,480
Changing her environment

112
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:21,858
only makes her more
confused and frightened.

113
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:24,318
I don't want to make it
any harder for her, Alice.

114
00:07:25,319 --> 00:07:29,157
Besides, you said the police
would be watching our house, right?

115
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:32,493
Alice, that's enough.

116
00:07:33,244 --> 00:07:35,496
- [pensive music plays]
- [sighs]

117
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,039
I'm sorry, Uncle. [sniffles]

118
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:39,959
Edong hurt you because of me.

119
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:42,170
[exhales]

120
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:45,089
Alice, I'm still alive, aren't I?

121
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:48,009
And if that happens again,

122
00:07:48,509 --> 00:07:50,094
I'll still do what I did.

123
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:53,639
I'll protect my grandson, Seth.

124
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:59,729
[pensive music continues]

125
00:08:01,105 --> 00:08:02,356
[sniffles]

126
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:07,195
[Alice sobs softly]

127
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:09,155
[music fades]

128
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:15,077
Erica…

129
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:23,002
Do you think he'll
come back for… for Althea?

130
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:32,136
Even I can't predict Edong's next move.

131
00:08:33,095 --> 00:08:35,056
At this point, anything is possible.

132
00:08:36,557 --> 00:08:38,392
But, like I said,

133
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:41,312
we all need to be careful.

134
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:47,777
I have to go.

135
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:49,403
Thank you.

136
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:55,618
[poignant music playing]

137
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:10,007
[Edward] You don't have to thank me.

138
00:09:12,468 --> 00:09:14,512
[sniffles, exhales deeply]

139
00:09:15,763 --> 00:09:17,557
[chuckles softly]

140
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:21,102
I will never be able
to stop thanking you, Uncle,

141
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:23,229
for saving my son. [sobs softly]

142
00:09:23,312 --> 00:09:24,522
Not in this lifetime.

143
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:26,399
[Edward chuckles slightly]

144
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:30,444
Uh, by the way, Alice…

145
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:33,197
Did you get any new
information about Kyle?

146
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:34,532
[sighs]

147
00:09:34,615 --> 00:09:35,866
No.

148
00:09:37,285 --> 00:09:39,370
But, um, we're investigating

149
00:09:39,453 --> 00:09:42,456
and now we're focusing
on his high school friends.

150
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:46,502
Maybe I can talk to Kyle's mother again.

151
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:49,755
- I might be able to get some information--
- No, no, no. Please, uncle…

152
00:09:49,839 --> 00:09:51,257
We can handle it.

153
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:52,508
But, Alice--

154
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:55,136
I don't want you to get hurt again.

155
00:09:55,219 --> 00:09:56,971
I don't want you to get involved, uncle.

156
00:09:58,389 --> 00:10:04,020
[poignant music continues, fades]

157
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:05,479
There's no movement here.

158
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:08,733
Ryan already
checked the list of the injured.

159
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:11,152
Mostly smoke inhalation.

160
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:14,530
One of them has a burn scar,
but on the arm, not the back.

161
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:16,157
[sighs]

162
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,366
So another dead end?

163
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:20,077
I'll call you back.

164
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:24,624
[somber music playing]

165
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:35,301
Any update about Cornelio?

166
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:37,386
Nothing.

167
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:39,263
Two days already, nothing.

168
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:43,559
We're trying to contact Edong.

169
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:47,480
We texted him, called him,
but I guess he doesn't want to be reached.

170
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:50,816
The police still can't find him either.

171
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:53,694
That must be our family's superpower.

172
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:55,071
Suddenly disappearing.

173
00:10:55,696 --> 00:10:56,822
First, my father.

174
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:58,115
Second, my brother.

175
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:02,536
[somber music continues]

176
00:11:03,245 --> 00:11:04,497
You seem drunk.

177
00:11:05,956 --> 00:11:07,124
You think?

178
00:11:08,459 --> 00:11:09,960
Of course, I've had a lot.

179
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:14,799
[phone clicks]

180
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:21,263
- [music turns suspenseful]
- [phone clicking]

181
00:11:37,696 --> 00:11:42,827
[suspenseful music continues]

182
00:11:45,788 --> 00:11:47,790
[music turns dramatic]

183
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:48,833
[men grunting]

184
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:50,167
[man 1] Call some officer already!

185
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:52,002
What are you waiting for?!
Just standing there watching?!

186
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:54,547
[men grunting]

187
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:55,923
- [man 2] Hey!
- [man 1] What now, Edong?!

188
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,550
[man 2] Hey! Stop that!

189
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,260
We already caught Edong!

190
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:05,182
- [men grunting]
- [dramatic music continues]

191
00:12:05,266 --> 00:12:06,434
[music ends]

192
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:07,977
[Lucas groans]

193
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:11,730
- [Erica] Can you manage?
- [Lucas] Hmm?

194
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:14,150
[Erica sighs]

195
00:12:33,627 --> 00:12:34,628
[Erica grunts]

196
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:36,046
- [groans]
- [Erika gasps]

197
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:41,093
[gentle music playing]

198
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:53,814
- [phone chimes]
- [music fades]

199
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:56,609
- [Lucas breathes deeply]
- [exhales]

200
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:07,161
- [Lucas groans]
- [Erika grunts]

201
00:13:08,078 --> 00:13:09,246
[groans]

202
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:11,624
[sighs heavily]

203
00:13:18,422 --> 00:13:19,924
[slurs] I don't know what to do anymore.

204
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:26,263
That was my plan.

205
00:13:27,264 --> 00:13:31,977
Get Edong out of jail, then start again.

206
00:13:37,566 --> 00:13:39,193
Now all of that is gone.

207
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,577
You can make a new plan.

208
00:13:50,871 --> 00:13:52,373
You've done it before.

209
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:54,917
You changed your life.

210
00:13:57,044 --> 00:13:58,587
You can do it again.

211
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:01,757
Alone?

212
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:06,095
[inhales sharply] Is that what
you're saying, that I do it alone?

213
00:14:10,307 --> 00:14:14,019
I could barely handle
it when I did it alone before.

214
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:18,315
I only did it for Edong.

215
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:23,195
[sighs] But I don't know if
I even want to do that again.

216
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:29,785
[melancholic music playing]

217
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:32,246
Turns out we're alike.

218
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:39,545
Left Amurao to start over in Manila.

219
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:44,341
[melancholic music continues]

220
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:48,762
I know how hard that was.

221
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:53,726
But we both did it.

222
00:14:58,939 --> 00:15:00,190
Imagine that.

223
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,528
The two outcasts from Amurao,

224
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:07,072
became successful on their own.

225
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,953
[melancholic music playing]

226
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:19,543
[young Erica sobbing]

227
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:22,838
[Lucas] I saw you…

228
00:15:24,882 --> 00:15:27,217
in an alley in Manila.

229
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:28,886
[running footsteps]

230
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:34,600
You were lying on the street, unconscious.

231
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:45,110
[melancholic music continues]

232
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:54,036
I left money in your hand.

233
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:05,631
[melancholic music continues]

234
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,555
[Erica] <i>Back when I had nothing,</i>

235
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:16,600
<i>someone gave me 50 pesos.</i>

236
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:23,065
<i>I didn't see who he was.</i>

237
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:24,400
<i>But whoever he was…</i>

238
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:28,988
<i>he was the one who saved my life.</i>

239
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,408
That was you?

240
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:35,619
Lucas…

241
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:40,416
[melancholic music continues]

242
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:47,047
[phone buzzing]

243
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:50,884
[music becomes tense]

244
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:56,640
[buzzing continues]

245
00:16:59,309 --> 00:17:02,604
[buzzing continues]

246
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:08,652
[buzzing continues]

247
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,073
- [man 1] Come here.
- [man 2] You bastard!

248
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:14,658
Hey! That's enough!

249
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:16,118
We caught Edong!

250
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,371
[music fades]

251
00:17:20,956 --> 00:17:22,750
You guys are acting like fools!

252
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,168
Does he look like Edong?!

253
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:25,586
You can see it, right?

254
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:28,172
He ran away suddenly
even though we told him to stop.

255
00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:31,133
And the news said Edong
also wears a hoodie and a cap.

256
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:33,844
So you're going to hit
anyone dressed like this?

257
00:17:33,927 --> 00:17:37,639
Well, if it speeds up
catching that idiot Edong, why not?

258
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,600
[tense music continues]

259
00:17:39,683 --> 00:17:41,810
- [line ringing]
- Please, pick up.

260
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:45,314
- [sighs]
- [ringing continues]

261
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:48,817
- [ringing continues]
- [music fades]

262
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:49,818
Mel?

263
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:51,737
[phone ringing fades]

264
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,322
Alice.

265
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:55,741
[sighs] Can't sleep?

266
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:58,077
Yeah.

267
00:17:59,244 --> 00:18:00,204
You?

268
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,664
I just woke up.

269
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:03,791
[sighs]

270
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:05,709
I didn't want to.

271
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:08,670
I wanted to continue that dream about…

272
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,464
that day at the market.

273
00:18:10,964 --> 00:18:12,758
When I got lost.

274
00:18:12,841 --> 00:18:16,345
I just want to find out who took me.

275
00:18:20,724 --> 00:18:22,684
[sighs]

276
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:25,437
We're surrounded by villains.

277
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:29,942
[foreboding music playing]

278
00:18:30,025 --> 00:18:31,902
We're surrounded by evil.

279
00:18:36,156 --> 00:18:37,533
[Mel] Do you feel it too?

280
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:42,621
We're surrounded by
people who want to punish us,

281
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:45,207
who want to torture and scare us.

282
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:51,213
[foreboding music continues]

283
00:18:51,296 --> 00:18:55,217
And I feel like we're just waiting
for whoever gets to us first.

284
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:59,429
[foreboding music intensifies]

285
00:18:59,513 --> 00:19:00,556
[thuds]

286
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:03,225
[grunting loudly]

287
00:19:04,434 --> 00:19:05,686
Fucking bitch!

288
00:19:05,769 --> 00:19:07,271
[clatters]

289
00:19:07,354 --> 00:19:08,856
You're nothing without me!

290
00:19:08,939 --> 00:19:10,732
I'll ruin you!

291
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:14,820
And I'll make sure you fucking pay!

292
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:25,038
[foreboding music continues]

293
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,924
Please forgive me.

294
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:40,012
[sobs] Please forgive me.

295
00:19:42,347 --> 00:19:43,974
I know.

296
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:45,809
This is all a test.

297
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:49,229
That is part of my mission.

298
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:52,024
It proves that I'm on the right path.

299
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:56,695
The demon brought down angels

300
00:19:56,778 --> 00:19:59,364
to protect the sinful.

301
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,076
But I won't stop.

302
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:07,915
I won't give up.

303
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:14,755
[foreboding music continues]

304
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:22,512
I won't stop until I do what I need to do.

305
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:24,765
Fuck!

306
00:20:27,601 --> 00:20:33,690
[music turns sinister]

307
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:48,622
[eerie whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]

308
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:58,257
[whistling continues]

309
00:21:01,551 --> 00:21:05,264
[suspenseful music playing]

310
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:08,558
[whistling continues]

311
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:37,337
[suspenseful music continues]

312
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:52,227
[suspenseful music crescendos]

313
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:56,273
[Erica] <i>He's no longer</i>
<i>the brother that Lucas knew.</i>

314
00:21:56,356 --> 00:21:57,649
<i>He's out of his mind.</i>

315
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:59,568
<i>Aren't the police looking for him?</i>

316
00:21:59,651 --> 00:22:00,944
- [screams]
- [chuckling]

317
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:02,654
<i>We can still solve Louisa's case.</i>

318
00:22:02,738 --> 00:22:04,865
[Marco] <i>How long will</i>
<i>you claim that Edong is innocent?</i>

319
00:22:04,948 --> 00:22:07,075
[Erica] <i>I want to do the right thing!</i>

320
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:09,661
<i>Kyle?</i>

321
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:13,623
- [grunts]
- [muffled screaming]

322
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:16,918
<i>[Edong] And you,</i>
<i>you've been there a long time,</i>

323
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:20,213
<i>convincing everyone</i>
<i>that everything is normal and safe.</i>

324
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:23,258
<i>But we both know no one is safe from you.</i>

325
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:25,302
[chuckling]

326
00:22:25,385 --> 00:22:28,055
<i>You can't stop me from getting Alice,</i>

327
00:22:28,138 --> 00:22:31,224
<i>nor Mel, nor Beth, nor Erica.</i>

328
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:34,186
<i>I will stand on top of your dead body</i>

329
00:22:34,269 --> 00:22:36,271
<i>if that's what it takes.</i>
